# MATAM Car System — Server installation guide

You've been given a folder called `matam_server`. It contains everything
needed to run the MATAM Car System backend on **any Windows PC**. Nothing
Intel-specific, no external dependencies, no internet access required
after the initial folder copy.

---

## What you get

```
matam_server/
├── pocketbase.exe            The backend server itself
├── pb_public/                The HTML web app (served by pocketbase.exe)
│   └── index.html
├── pb_data/                  Database + logs (auto-populated on first run)
├── collections_schema.json   The DB schema used on first setup
├── deploy_config.env         Edit BEFORE first install to change defaults
├── install_server.cmd        <-- RUN THIS ONCE to set everything up
├── setup_schema.ps1          Called by install_server.cmd (no need to run manually)
├── start_pocketbase.cmd      Manual start (installer already auto-registers this)
├── enable_autostart.cmd      Registers Windows auto-start (installer runs this)
├── disable_autostart.cmd     Un-registers auto-start
├── enable_firewall.cmd       Adds Windows Firewall inbound rule (run as admin)
├── disable_firewall.cmd      Removes the firewall rule (run as admin)
├── show_server_url.cmd       Prints the URLs to share with clients
├── change_admin_password.cmd Interactive password change for the admin UI
└── README_SERVER.md          You are reading this
```

## Prerequisites

- Windows 10 or later
- ~50 MB free disk space
- PowerShell 5+ (built into every modern Windows)
- **No Python, no Node.js, no Docker, no Java** — nothing else to install

## First-time setup — 3 steps

### 1. (Optional) Edit `deploy_config.env`

Change `ADMIN_PASSWORD` to something private if you don't want the default.
Everything else is auto-detected.

### 2. Double-click `install_server.cmd`

It will ask "Create the initial admin manager account?" — say **Y** in
almost all cases (say **N** only if you want to bootstrap users purely
via the PocketBase admin UI).

The installer takes ~10 seconds and does everything:
- stops any old PocketBase
- creates the PocketBase superuser (for the admin console)
- starts PocketBase in the background
- applies the DB schema (`vehicles`, `archive`, `leads`, `users`)
- creates **one** manager account (`admin@matam.local`) that you use to
  log into the MATAM app itself. From there, the manager creates real
  employee accounts through the app's built-in User Management section.
- registers Windows auto-start so PocketBase comes back after every reboot
- prints the URLs to share with clients

The **same password** is used for both accounts (superuser and manager),
so you only need to remember one. Set it in `deploy_config.env`
(default is `matam2026`).

### 3. Right-click `enable_firewall.cmd` → **Run as administrator**

This is a one-time step. Without it, other PCs on the same network can't
reach the server. You need admin rights just for this one command.

That's the whole install. The server is now running and will keep running
across reboots.

## Sharing the URL with clients

Run `show_server_url.cmd` at any time. It prints the URLs like:

```
http://192.168.1.42:8090/       <-- give this to LAN clients
http://myserver:8090/           <-- short hostname, works on some LANs
```

Give any one of those URLs to your client machines. They just paste it in
Chrome / Edge / Firefox. There is nothing to install on the client side
(see `client/README_CLIENT.md` for optional desktop shortcut).

## Day-to-day management

| I want to... | Do this |
|---|---|
| **Add a new employee** | Log into the MATAM app as a manager → **Settings → User Management → Add User**. This is the primary flow. |
| Reset an employee's password | Same place — click the key icon next to the user → set a new password |
| Change someone's role (manager ↔ agent) | Same place — pick a new role in the user row |
| See who's using it, watch logs, low-level DB inspection | Open http://127.0.0.1:8090/_/ on the server PC (advanced) |
| Change your OWN admin password | Log into the app, **Settings → User Management → Reset my password**, OR double-click `change_admin_password.cmd` |
| Manual backup | Zip the entire `pb_data` folder while server is running (SQLite WAL is safe) |
| Restore | Stop PocketBase, replace `pb_data` folder, start again |
| Move server to another PC | Zip the whole folder, unzip on new PC, run `install_server.cmd` |
| Temporarily stop the server | `taskkill /IM pocketbase.exe /F` |
| Un-register auto-start | Double-click `disable_autostart.cmd` |
| Uninstall completely | Kill pocketbase.exe, run `disable_autostart.cmd`, run `disable_firewall.cmd`, delete the folder |

## Nothing is hardcoded

- **Server hostname / IP**: never hardcoded anywhere. Discovered at runtime.
- **Admin email/password**: read from `deploy_config.env` (or defaults if the file is missing).
- **Bind address**: read from `deploy_config.env`, defaults to `0.0.0.0:8090`
  (any interface, port 8090).
- **Client URL**: clients open the server URL via a bookmark or a shortcut
  they create locally with `install_client_shortcut.cmd URL`. If you move
  the server, clients just update their bookmark.

## Troubleshooting

**"pocketbase.exe not found"** — check the folder you extracted to;
`pocketbase.exe` must sit next to `install_server.cmd`.

**"superuser upsert failed"** — usually means PocketBase is still holding
the DB. Kill it manually: `taskkill /IM pocketbase.exe /F` then re-run.

**"PocketBase did not become ready within 30 seconds"** — port 8090 may
already be in use. Change `BIND=0.0.0.0:8091` in `deploy_config.env` and
re-run the installer.

**Client can hit `/api/health` but the app pages are blank** — probably
missing `pb_public\index.html`. Copy the app HTML into `pb_public\` and
refresh the browser.

**Client on another PC can't reach the server at all** —
- Both PCs on same LAN / VPN?
- `enable_firewall.cmd` was run as admin?
- Try the IP form (`http://192.168.1.42:8090/`) instead of hostname
- On the server PC, run `show_server_url.cmd` to confirm the current URL

## Security notes for production

- Change the default admin password (`deploy_config.env` or `change_admin_password.cmd`).
- Change or delete the demo user accounts through the admin UI.
- Consider putting the server behind HTTPS if you'll be exposing it beyond
  a trusted LAN. PocketBase supports Let's Encrypt automatic HTTPS with
  `--https 0.0.0.0:443` if the machine has a public DNS name; for LAN-only
  deployments plain HTTP is normally fine.
